    <div class="section firstReview">
      

<div id="review_62353748" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/62353748" />
    <a title="Renee" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/2012116-renee"><img alt="Renee" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1555514526p2/2012116.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/62353748?book_show_action=true">Jul 06, 2009</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Renee" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Renee" href="/user/show/2012116-renee">Renee</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer62353748" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3902462358598322201">A heavy subject for any writer, Peter Hollings handles the evolution of man very well. Some parts were a little too technical for me, but that&apos;s a personal thing. I am not and will never be a scientist for obvious reasons. <br/><br/>I found his theories very thought provoking and was in awe at the research involved in this book. Mr. Hollings writing style was clear and concise, intended to engage the reader rather than talk at them. I respect that in an author writing non-fiction. You may be writing about</span>
  <span id="freeText3902462358598322201" style="display:none">A heavy subject for any writer, Peter Hollings handles the evolution of man very well. Some parts were a little too technical for me, but that's a personal thing. I am not and will never be a scientist for obvious reasons. <br /><br />I found his theories very thought provoking and was in awe at the research involved in this book. Mr. Hollings writing style was clear and concise, intended to engage the reader rather than talk at them. I respect that in an author writing non-fiction. You may be writing about fact but you still must engage your reader. This book does that very well.<br /><br />No matter what your theory on our evolution and how we came to be, I recommend you pick up this book. It sparks an interesting debate and raises some valid points about many theories. It's also a good read. <br /><br />Well done Peter, I enjoyed it more than I expected. It has been an excellent tool for engaging my kids in discussion about the topic, and educating them on science and history relating to humanity and it's evolution. It will be the starting point for getting them to read other theories and study their origins. That is invaluable to me as a parent. <br /><br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="3902462358598322201" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


